Definition.WordDefinition: Marysole \Ma"ry*sole\, n. [Mary, the proper name + sole the fish.] (Zo["o]l.) A large British fluke, or flounder ({Rhombus megastoma}); -- called also {carter}, and {whiff}. [1913 Webster]

Definition.WordDefinition:
Daddy longlegs \Dad"dy long"legs`\ 1. (Zo["o]l.) An arachnidan of the genus {Phalangium}, and allied genera, having a small body and four pairs of long legs; -- called also {harvestman}, {carter}, and {grandfather longlegs}. [1913 Webster]
2. (Zo["o]l.) A name applied to many species of dipterous insects of the genus {Tipula}, and allied genera, with slender bodies, and very long, slender legs; the crane fly; -- called also {father longlegs}. [1913 Webster]

Definition.WordDefinition:
Carter \Cart"er\, n. 1. A charioteer. [Obs.] --Chaucer. [1913 Webster]
2. A man who drives a cart; a teamster. [1913 Webster]
3. (Zo["o]l.) (a) Any species of {Phalangium}; -- also called {harvestman}. (b) A British fish; the whiff. [1913 Webster]

Carter n 1: Englishman and Egyptologist who in 1922 discovered and excavated the tomb of Tutankhamen (1873-1939) [syn: {Howard Carter}] 2: 39th President of the United States (1924-) [syn: {Jimmy Carter}, {James Earl Carter}, {James Earl Carter Jr.}, {President Carter}] 3: a hauler of garbage; "there is a web site where licensed carters and would-be customers can make connections" [syn: {garbage carter}, {garbage hauler}] 4: someone whose work is driving carts
